724153f-b.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - Houston Street (West)
724153f-b.text:
(1)
Washington Street, west side, from West Houston (formerly
Hammersley) Street to Leroy Street, inclusive.
September 30, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, to Leroy Street and north. The northern end of the
new St. John's Park Freight Terminal will be at Clarkson
Street, but the buildings on the west side of Washington Street
north from that point are being razed for the building of
the railroad's elevated roadbed.
June 30, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

724147f-c.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - Houston Street (West)
724147f-c.text:
Vashington Street, north from W. Houston Street, showing
mainly thne west side of this thoroughfare. In the foreground are
a row of stables extending to Clarkson Street. In 1930 these
buildings will be razed for the St. Johns Park Freight Terminal;
thig site being the proposed northern prtion of same.
Buildings north of Clarkson Street will be demolished at
same time and the elevated roadbed of the New York Gentral Railroad
erecten there. The street car tracks shown will be removed by
the W.P.a. in l937.
View No. 3 snows buildings at the N.W . corner of Washington
(right) and W. Houston (left) Streets.
View 1: May 12, 1927
View 2: July 23, 1930
View 3: Oct. 21, 1927
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIOiS

724530f-a.title: Manhattan: Houston Street (West - Washington Street
724530f-a.text:
Houston Street, western section (formerly Hammersley Street), north
side, from Washington to West Streets, inclusive. A view of the
block which will be permanently closed when the new St. John's
Park Freight Terminal is built in 1933-34.
October 21, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
